Reasoning: The paper deals with a model of flocking behavior in birds, which involves adjusting velocities based on neighbor interactions. This falls under the category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and social networks (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the convergence of the flocking network, which involves analyzing the dynamics of a large number of interacting agents, making it relevant to the category of distributed systems (cs.DS) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper introduces new techniques that may be of broader interest to the circuit complexity community, making it relevant to the category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
